      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "By incorporating a priori knowledge about the specificity of derivatizing matrices and reagents, such as FMP-10 and AMPP, respectively, Met-ID uses the chemical structures in the form of simplified molecular-input line-entry system (SMILES) to parse the HMDB and LIPID MAPS and more effectively differentiate between potential candidates and noncandidates.",
