    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/software-plugin-development/000",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "To enhance its versatility, Met-ID allows users to customize their own versions... Met-ID also provides tools for calculating and supporting the different masses added by other derivatizing matrices. Additionally, since some metabolites are not included in the HMDB, Met-ID enables users to add new entries, ensuring the software remains adaptable to specific research needs.",
      "asbval:note": "Paper confirms extensibility and customization without core modification, but describes this as direct database/configuration editing rather than formal 'plugin module' registration. The mechanism is configuration-driven (adding matrices, metabolites, MS2 spectra) but not explicitly framed as a plugin architecture with a plugin registry.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1021-acs-analchem-5c00633",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "partial",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "software-plugin-development",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "research_question",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "Extend a scientific software tool by creating and registering new plugin modules or configuration files that add support for novel reagents, matrices, or analysis parameters without modifying the core codebase.",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000361"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T14:07:27.647665+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000339"
      }
    },
    {
      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/software-plugin-development/001",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "Met-ID also provides tools for calculating and supporting the different masses added by other derivatizing matrices... FMP-10 is a suitable matrix for experiments targeting neurotransmitters, and the base version of Met-ID is optimized for its use. However, Met-ID also provides tools for calculating and supporting the different masses added by other derivatizing matrices.",
      "asbval:note": "Paper confirms Met-ID supports alternative matrices (TAHS is mentioned in introduction as an example of reactive matrices), but the mechanism is described as user-customizable database editing and configuration, not formal plugin registration. The example of TAHS is mentioned as context for derivatizing agents but not demonstrated as a worked example of adding it to Met-ID.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1021-acs-analchem-5c00633",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "partial",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "software-plugin-development",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "skill_bundle",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "scope",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "When you have a scientific software tool (e.g., Met-ID) that is architected to support plugins or configuration-driven modules, and you need to register and apply a novel reagent, derivatizing matrix, or analytical method (e.g., TAHS instead of FMP-10) that is not yet bundled in ",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000361"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
      "prov:wasGeneratedAtTime": "2026-06-15T14:07:27.647665+00:00",
      "sepio:credibility_status": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/SEPIO_0000339"
      }
    },
